      "date": "2014-07-22 22:27:24.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nHumm patch-set #1 causes SLES builds only to fail due (obddev->u.cli.cl_close_lock->rpcl_mutex.owner == current_thread_info()) test reported to be with \"different pointer types\" and cast required .... Seems that with recent Kernels, owner field of struct mutex is no longer a (struct thread_info) * ! May be a (struct task_struct *) ?",
