        "subject": "LU-5349 llite: avoid self-deadlock around inflight RPC mutex",
        "message": "LU-5349 llite: avoid self-deadlock around inflight RPC mutex\n\nSince clear_inode() can be called as part of memory reclaim it need\nto ensure that current thread is not already owner of mutex to\nserialize inflight RPCs or it will self-deadlock when trying to\nacquire it to send more close RPC.\n\nSigned-off-by: Bruno Faccini <bruno.faccini@intel.com>\nChange-Id: Iff7f7f5f9fc783823bda804c7d41a93eaa83fa7f\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
